Indexes are tags used to store and search document information, such as customer IDs, dates, or other metadata that are relevant to business users.

The **Custom indexes** and **System indexes** tables list all available document indexes for the current document category, more specifically:

- **Custom indexes **are placeholders for business information, such as customer IDs, customer dates, locations, etc.

- **System indexes **contain information coming from the Doxee Platform that cannot be changed by users, such as system IDs, system dates, system endpoint names, etc.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The indexes tables display the following columns:

**Column**

**Description**

**Index**

Name of the index

**Type**

Data type of the index

> Warning

Aliases for indexes must follow these rules:

- Aliases are case-sensitive.

- Aliases may contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), underscores (_) and hyphens (-).

- Aliases may start with a letter or a number.

- Aliases may contain at least 1 and up to 100 characters.

**Scope**

Number of document categories that the index is associated with

> Note

If no indexes have been defined yet, these tables are empty. For more information, see [Adding a new index](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-indexes#adding-a-new-index) below.

## Adding a new index
- Edit the required document category, as described in [Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Managing Document Categories](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-document-categories).

- Click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) **Add index **on the top-right of the **Custom indexes** or **System indexes **table, depending on the type of index you want to create. 

A new entry named *undefined *is created; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see [Editing a custom index](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-indexes#editing-a-custom-index) and [Editing a system index](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-indexes#editing-a-system-index) below.

> Index type limits

The number of available custom indexes is limited according to their type and will be validated by the system during the configuration. The drop-down menu for selecting the index type will only display types which still have free slots.

For example, if the Digital Archiving Store already contains five indexes of the type clob, the drop-down menu wont display the type clob when adding another custom index:

![Custom indexes list showing various index types and a warning for Clob6.](data:image/png;base64,)

The index type limits are as follows:

**Type**

**Maximum number of indexes**

String

50

Number

10

Date

10

Time

25

Clob

5

## Editing a custom index
- Edit the required document category, as described in [Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Managing Document Categories](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-document-categories).

- Move your mouse pointer over the row corresponding to the index that you want to edit. The ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**More**)  icon is displayed on the right

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**More**) and select ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  (**Edit**) from the list of available actions. The fields are now editable:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Configure the required parameters:

**Field**

**Description**

**Index**

Name of the index

**Type**

Select the data type from the drop-down menu; the possible values are:

**String**

- **Number**

- **Date**

- **Time **

- **Clob**

- Click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  to save the configuration.

> Warning

Indexes can only be edited or deleted if the Digital Archiving Store configuration has not yet been saved (see 

[Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Editor](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-editor)).

Once the configuration has been saved, it's no longer possible to edit or delete indexes.

## Editing a system index
- Edit the required document category, as described in [Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Managing Document Categories](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-document-categories). 

- Move your mouse pointer over the row corresponding to the new index. The ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**More**)icon is displayed on the right:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  (**More**) and select ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  **Edit **from the list of available actions. The fields are now editable:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Configure the required parameters:

**Field**

**Description**

**Index**

Name of the index

**Type**

Select the system property that will be associated with the index from the drop-down menu.

> Note

For more information, see [List of available system properties](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-indexes#list-of-available-system-properties) below.

- Click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) to save the configuration.

> Warning

Indexes can only be edited or deleted if the Digital Archiving Store configuration has not yet been saved (see [Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Editor](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-editor)).

Once the configuration has been saved, it's no longer possible to edit or delete indexes.

## Deleting an index
- Edit the required document category, as described in [Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Managing Document Categories](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-managing-document-categories).

- Move your mouse pointer over the row corresponding to the index that you want to delete. The ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) icon is displayed on the right

- Click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  (**More**) and select ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**Delete**) from the list of available actions. The index is permanently removed from the current category.

> Warning

Indexes can only be edited or deleted if the Digital Archiving Store configuration has not yet been saved (see 

[Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Editor](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-stores-user-guide-doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-editor)).

Once the configuration has been saved, it's no longer possible to edit or delete indexes.

The operation cannot be undone.
